# Emoji

Use emojis consistently in user-facing content and in code.

## When to use

- **Reactions**: Use for bot message reactions, reaction roles, and feedback (e.g. success/error).
- **Messages/embeds**: Use sparingly to emphasize status, actions, or sections (e.g. ‚úÖ ‚ùå üìå).
- **Permissions/features**: When referring to emoji in config (e.g. `permissions.json`, schema), use the same format the rest of the project uses (e.g. `emoji`, `Emoji` field, or Discord custom emoji format).

## How to represent

- **Unicode emojis**: Use the actual character or a named constant when the same emoji is reused (e.g. success, error).
- **Discord custom emojis**: Use format `<:name:id>` or the identifier your schema expects (e.g. `legacy_emoji` as default in migrations).
